meta-rpi4-qt6-template
======================

This layer provides a minimal Qt 6 image and example application for the
Raspberry Pi 4 64-bit target.

It is intended as a small starting point for framebuffer-based Qt 6
applications on Yocto Project scarthgap.


Dependencies
============

This layer depends on the following layers:

* poky/meta
* meta-raspberrypi
* meta-qt6
* meta-openembedded/meta-oe
* meta-openembedded/meta-python
* meta-openembedded/meta-networking

The layer metadata declares the direct layer dependencies below:

* core
* raspberrypi
* qt6-layer


Provided Recipes
================

rpi4-qt6-image
--------------

`rpi4-qt6-image` is a minimal bootable Raspberry Pi 4 image with:

* Qt 6 runtime packages
* OpenSSH server support
* NetworkManager and Wi-Fi support
* Fontconfig with DejaVu and Korean TrueType fonts
* `qt6-hello-world` preinstalled
* Qt 6 SDK generation support through `populate_sdk_qt6_base`

Build the image:

    source sources/poky/oe-init-build-env build-rpi4
    bitbake rpi4-qt6-image

Build the SDK:

    source sources/poky/oe-init-build-env build-rpi4
    bitbake rpi4-qt6-image -c populate_sdk


qt6-hello-world
---------------

`qt6-hello-world` is a simple Qt Creator/CMake based Qt Widgets application.
It is installed to:

    /usr/bin/qt6-hello-world

The recipe also installs and enables a systemd service:

    qt6-hello-world.service

The service starts the application after boot with the Linux framebuffer Qt
platform plugin:

    QT_QPA_PLATFORM=linuxfb
    QT_QPA_GENERIC_PLUGINS=libinput

Check the service on the target:

    systemctl status qt6-hello-world

Restart the application:

    systemctl restart qt6-hello-world


Layer Setup
===========

Add this layer to your build configuration:

    bitbake-layers add-layer sources/meta-rpi4-qt6-template

Make sure the Raspberry Pi 4 64-bit machine is selected:

    MACHINE ??= "raspberrypi4-64"

For HDMI displays that show TV-style margins or blurry framebuffer output, the
Raspberry Pi firmware overscan margin can be disabled in `local.conf`:

    DISABLE_OVERSCAN = "1"


Notes
=====

The example application is intentionally small. Replace the source under
`recipes-qt/qt6-hello-world/files/qt6-hello-world/` with a Qt Creator CMake
project when using this layer as an application template.

Do not commit Qt Creator local files or build outputs such as:

* `CMakeLists.txt.user`
* `build/`
* `build-*`
